==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Indo-do-Chinese languages
<hw>In`do-do-Chinese languages</hw>. <def>A family of languages, mostly
of the isolating type, although some are agglutinative, spoken in the
great area extending from northern India in the west to Formosa in the
east and from Central Asia in the north to the Malay Peninsula in the
south.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Indocibility</ent>⟦br⟧
